==Drops==
Players must do at least 2 damage to Zalcano's shield to be eligible for drops, and 31 combined damage to be eligible for uniques and pet.

Drops from the main table and from the tertiary table scale with the player's points from the kill. The points are calculated as shown in the formula below. For the tertiary table, the damage to hitpoints and shield are capped to a max of 400 and 300 respectively, for a maximum of 1,000 points.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Lenny|url=https://twitter.com/JagexLenny/status/1188831844722270208|date=28 October 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.md/lkmqz|archivedate=19 November 2019|quote="Points" get calculated based on the damage you dealt to Zalcano's health plus two times the damage you dealt to her armour. Given those numbers, you'd have 550 points of a total possible 1000, and would have a 1/2175 roll at the pet, for example.}}

<math>\begin{align}
P_{M} &= H + 2 \times S \\
P_{T} &= \min(H, 400) + 2 \times \min(S, 300)
\end{align}</math>

Where <math display="inline">P_{M}</math> is points towards main table, <math display="inline">P_{T}</math> is points towards tertiary table, <math display="inline">H</math> is damage to hitpoints and <math display="inline">S</math> is damage to shield.

The MVP, the player who deals the most damage to Zalcano, will also receive an additional 10% (rounded up) of their non-unique loot.

Players can speak to [[Rhiannon]] to switch between receiving item drops or Mining experience. Experience scales with contribution to approximately <math display="inline">P_{M} + P_{T} \times 5</math>{{Fact|Matches in-game testing but has not been confirmed}}  and is affected by the experience bonus of the [[Prospector kit]]. This does not affect the guaranteed drops or the unique drop table, which is always rolled regardless of choosing items or experience. 

